From 92e0782139e060a0fa22230c2a7f7b7aee3165d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Glen Kirkham <Glenkirkham@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 22:16:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(studio-auth): remove local dev auth popup and add
 unlock flow

- Bypass access gate entirely when running in dev mode on loopback
  (127.0.0.1/::1) so the browser never sees a bare 401 in local dev
- Replace plain-text 401 page with an in-app HTML unlock form so
  Safari and other browsers cannot trigger a native credentials dialog
- Add POST /api/studio/access/unlock endpoint: validates token, sets
  studio_access cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict), returns JSON
- API routes still receive JSON 401 with a clear hint (no popup)
- Production/public-host protection unchanged: token always enforced
  when not in dev+loopback mode
- Add README troubleshooting section covering why popup happens,
  how to disable for local dev, and how to unlock via form or curl

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
