 server/access-gate.js | 204 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 server/index.js       |  10 ++-
 3 files changed, 264 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index bd2b441..147a809 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -202,6 +202,63 @@ If the UI loads but Connect fails, the problem is usually on the Studio -> Gatew
 - `401 Studio access token required` usually means `STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN` is enabled and the request is missing the expected `studio_access` cookie.
 - Helpful proxy error codes include `studio.gateway_url_missing`, `studio.gateway_token_missing`, `studio.upstream_error`, and `studio.upstream_closed`.
 
+### Browser shows a login/auth popup on localhost
+
+**Why it happens:** If `STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN` is set in your shell environment or a `.env.local`
+file, the studio access gate activates and returns a `401` for unauthenticated page requests.
+Some browsers (notably Safari on macOS) display a native credentials dialog for any bare 401,
+even without a `WWW-Authenticate` header.
+
+**How to disable for local dev (recommended):**
+
+The server automatically bypasses the access gate when running in dev mode on a loopback
+address (`127.0.0.1` / `::1` / `localhost`). All you need to do is make sure
+`STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN` is **not** set in your shell when running `npm run dev`:
+
+```bash
+# Check if it's set
+echo $STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN
+
+# Unset for the current session
+unset STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN
+
+# Or run dev without it
+STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN= npm run dev
+```
+
+Alternatively, leave the line commented out in `.env.local`:
+
+```env
+# STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN=   ← keep this commented out for local dev
+```
+
+**How to unlock if the token IS set:**
+
+If you need `STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN` set locally (e.g. testing production auth flow), the gate
+shows an in-app **Studio Locked** screen instead of a browser popup. Enter your token there
+and click **Unlock Studio** — it sets a `studio_access` cookie and reloads.
+
+You can also unlock via curl:
+
+```bash
+curl -s -c cookies.txt -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/studio/access/unlock \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"token":"your-token-here"}'
+# → {"ok":true}
+```
+
+**Verify the popup is gone:**
+
+```bash
+curl -I http://localhost:3000
+# Should NOT contain: WWW-Authenticate
+# Should return: 200 OK  (dev, no token set)
+#            or: 401 with HTML unlock page  (token set, not yet unlocked)
+```
+
+**Production / public host:** `STUDIO_ACCESS_TOKEN` is always enforced when binding to a
+public IP or hostname. The server refuses to start on a public host without it.
+
